verbose_text: Moreover, RT-qPCR analysis revealed that ZA (Cmax) did not decrease the total amount of both TGF-beta receptor type (types I and II) expression at the mRNA level (XREF_FIG, upper and lower graphs, respectively), suggesting that ZA (Cmax) suppressed the expression of TGF-beta type I receptor on the surface of hGFs.
evidence: expression of TGF-beta type I receptor
